<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 6:36AM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Foard and
Hardeman Counties through 715 AM CDT...
At 635 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southwest of Quanah, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Quanah, Chillicothe, Margaret, Goodlett, Medicine Mound, Copper
Breaks State Park, and Lazare.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
